[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Vanilla limits well building heavily — only one specific pump can be built, after a tech unlock, and the basic stone well isn't player-buildable at all. This mod opens both up as repeatable build crafts.[/size]

[size=3][b]Buildable wells[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Basic stone well[/b] — added to the wooden build desk from the start of the game. Costs 4 flitch and 4 stone.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Pump well[/b] — added to the same build desk. Spawns a pump on the closest existing stone well to you. Costs 8 flitch, 4 nails, and 2 iron details, matching vanilla. Repeatable, so every stone well you build can get a pump.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Removable[/b] — both wells can be deconstructed via the build desk's Remove button, returning half the build cost.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Progression[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Tech gate stays by default[/b] — the pump well stays locked behind the vanilla tech requirement until you research it.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Optional early unlock[/b] — flip a config toggle to drop the tech gate and build pumps from the start.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/60]I Build Where I Want[/url] — place buildables anywhere on the map. Drop wells wherever you want them.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/76]Where's Ma' Veggies[/url] — every veggie buyable from the gardener. Pairs well with abundant water sources.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/54]Apple Trees Enhanced[/url] — bigger, healthier apple orchards. More trees, more thirst for water.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — queue any craft and walk away. Handy for water pumping runs.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Compatibility[/b][/size]

[size=3]Built and tested against the latest Windows Steam build of Graveyard Keeper. Other storefronts and platforms aren't extensively tested — should generally work, but YMMV.[/size]

[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:[/size]

[code]...\steamapps\common\Graveyard Keeper\BepInEx[/code]

